com.turn.ttorrent.client.io

Class PeerMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.turn.ttorrent.client.io.PeerMessage
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PeerExtendedMessage, PeerHandshakeMessage, PeerMessage.AbstractPieceMessage, PeerMessage.BitfieldMessage, PeerMessage.ChokeMessage, PeerMessage.HaveMessage, PeerMessage.InterestedMessage, PeerMessage.KeepAliveMessage, PeerMessage.NotInterestedMessage, PeerMessage.UnchokeMessage

    public abstract class PeerMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    BitTorrent peer protocol messages representations.

    This class and its *Messages subclasses provide POJO representations of the peer protocol messages, along with easy parsing from an input ByteBuffer to quickly get a usable representation of an incoming message.

    See Also:
    BitTorrent peer wire protocol
